[% META
        title = "Template Documentation"
   description = "Documentation for system templates"
   roles = "admin,developer"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "templates"
   page_version = "1.02"
   last_updated = "Wed Oct 15 11:17:04 AM PDT 2025"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/documentation_tt_template.tt,v 0.02 11:17:04 2025/10/15 shanta Exp shanta - Theme-Compliant Documentation Template' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Documentation Page Title</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: 2025-10-15 | 
        Version: 3.0 | 
        Author: [Author Name] | 
        Status: [Status]
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Brief overview of what this documentation covers. This should be 1-2 sentences explaining the purpose and scope.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Requirement 1</li>
                <li>Requirement 2</li>
                <li>System access level needed</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Features</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Feature 1</strong>: Description of feature</li>
                <li><strong>Feature 2</strong>: Description of feature</li>
                <li><strong>Feature 3</strong>: Description of feature</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Getting Started</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 1: Initial Setup</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Detailed instructions for the first step.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Example code or command
example_command --parameter value
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 2: Configuration</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Instructions for configuration step.</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Configure option A</li>
                <li>Set parameter B</li>
                <li>Verify setting C</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 3: Verification</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">How to verify everything is working correctly.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Advanced Usage</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Advanced Feature 1</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Description and usage instructions for advanced features.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Integration with Other Systems</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">How this feature integrates with other parts of the application.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Troubleshooting</h2>
            
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: Common Issue 1</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Description of symptoms</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong> Step by step solution</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: Common Issue 2</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Description of symptoms</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong> Step by step solution</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Configuration Reference</h2>
            
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <tr>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Parameter</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Type</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Default</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">parameter_1</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">string</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">"default_value"</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Description of parameter</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">parameter_2</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">boolean</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">true</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Description of parameter</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div class="success" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <h2 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">See Also</h2>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><a href="/Documentation/related_doc_1" style="color: var(--link-color);">Related Documentation 1</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/Documentation/related_doc_2" style="color: var(--link-color);">Related Documentation 2</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/admin" style="color: var(--link-color);">Administrative Interface</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large); padding-top: var(--spacing-medium); border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
                <p>For technical support or questions about this documentation, contact the system administrator.</p>
                <p><em>This documentation is part of the Comserv system.</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- 
THEME COMPLIANCE NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS:

This template is fully theme-compliant using the actual Comserv theme system:

1. **CSS Variables Used**: All styling uses CSS custom properties from base.css:
   - --text-color, --background-color, --primary-color, --secondary-color
   - --header-font, --body-font, --font-size-* variables
   - --spacing-small, --spacing-medium, --spacing-large for consistent spacing
   - --border-color, --table-header-bg, --warning-color, --success-color, --info-color

2. **Layout System**: Uses the responsive grid system from layout.css:
   - .container for main content wrapper
   - .row for horizontal groupings
   - .col-100, .col-50 for responsive column layouts

3. **Color-Coded Content Blocks**: 
   - Warning blocks use --warning-color with left border accent
   - Info blocks use --info-color with left border accent  
   - Success blocks use --success-color with left border accent

4. **Responsive Design**: Layout automatically adapts on mobile using layout.css media queries

5. **Theme Variables Available**:
   From theme_definitions.json, any site can override:
   - Colors: primary-color, secondary-color, accent-color, text-color, etc.
   - Typography: header-font, body-font, font-size-base, font-size-large, etc.
   - UI Elements: button-bg, nav-bg, table-header-bg, border-color, etc.

6. **Cross-Theme Compatibility**: Works correctly with:
   - Default theme (standard blue/white)
   - CSC theme (cyan backgrounds)  
   - USBM theme (green accent colors)
   - APIS theme (yellow/orange beekeeping theme)
   - Any future themes added to theme_definitions.json

Usage: Replace placeholder content but maintain the CSS variable usage patterns.
-->